33# define SetKey \
34 RSA_set0_key(key, \
35 BN_bin2bn(n, sizeof(n)-1, NULL), \
36 BN_bin2bn(e, sizeof(e)-1, NULL), \
37 BN_bin2bn(d, sizeof(d)-1, NULL)); \
38 RSA_set0_factors(key, \
39 BN_bin2bn(p, sizeof(p)-1, NULL), \
40 BN_bin2bn(q, sizeof(q)-1, NULL)); \
41 RSA_set0_crt_params(key, \
42 BN_bin2bn(dmp1, sizeof(dmp1)-1, NULL), \
43 BN_bin2bn(dmq1, sizeof(dmq1)-1, NULL), \
44 BN_bin2bn(iqmp, sizeof(iqmp)-1, NULL)); \
45 memcpy(c, ctext_ex, sizeof(ctext_ex) - 1); \
46 return sizeof(ctext_ex) - 1;

214static int pad_unknown(void)
215{
216 unsigned long l;
217 while ((l = ERR_get_error()) != 0)
218 if (ERR_GET_REASON(l) == RSA_R_UNKNOWN_PADDING_TYPE)
219 return 1;
220 return 0;
221}
222
223static int rsa_setkey(RSA** key, unsigned char* ctext, int idx)
224{
225 int clen = 0;
226 *key = RSA_new();
227 switch (idx) {
228 case 0:
229 clen = key1(*key, ctext);
230 break;
231 case 1:
232 clen = key2(*key, ctext);
233 break;
234 case 2:
235 clen = key3(*key, ctext);
236 break;
237 }
238 return clen;
239}
240
241static int test_rsa_pkcs1(int idx)
242{
243 int ret = 0;
244 RSA *key;
245 unsigned char ptext[256];
246 unsigned char ctext[256];
247 static unsigned char ptext_ex[] = "\x54\x85\x9b\x34\x2c\x49\xea\x2a";
248 unsigned char ctext_ex[256];
249 int plen;
250 int clen = 0;
251 int num;
252
253 plen = sizeof(ptext_ex) - 1;
254 clen = rsa_setkey(&key, ctext_ex, idx);
255
256 num = RSA_public_encrypt(plen, ptext_ex, ctext, key,
257 RSA_PKCS1_PADDING);
258 if (!TEST_int_eq(num, clen))
259 goto err;
260
261 num = RSA_private_decrypt(num, ctext, ptext, key, RSA_PKCS1_PADDING);
262 if (!TEST_mem_eq(ptext, num, ptext_ex, plen))
263 goto err;
264
265 ret = 1;
266err:
267 RSA_free(key);
268 return ret;
269}

301static int test_rsa_oaep(int idx)
302{
303 int ret = 0;
304 RSA *key;
305 unsigned char ptext[256];
306 unsigned char ctext[256];
307 static unsigned char ptext_ex[] = "\x54\x85\x9b\x34\x2c\x49\xea\x2a";
308 unsigned char ctext_ex[256];
309 int plen;
310 int clen = 0;
311 int num;
312 int n;
313
314 plen = sizeof(ptext_ex) - 1;
315 clen = rsa_setkey(&key, ctext_ex, idx);
316
317 num = RSA_public_encrypt(plen, ptext_ex, ctext, key,
318 RSA_PKCS1_OAEP_PADDING);
319 if (num == -1 && pad_unknown()) {
320 TEST_info("Skipping: No OAEP support");
321 ret = 1;
322 goto err;
323 }
324 if (!TEST_int_eq(num, clen))
325 goto err;
326
327 num = RSA_private_decrypt(num, ctext, ptext, key,
328 RSA_PKCS1_OAEP_PADDING);
329 if (!TEST_mem_eq(ptext, num, ptext_ex, plen))
330 goto err;
331
332 /* Different ciphertexts. Try decrypting ctext_ex */
333 num = RSA_private_decrypt(clen, ctext_ex, ptext, key,
334 RSA_PKCS1_OAEP_PADDING);
335 if (!TEST_mem_eq(ptext, num, ptext_ex, plen))
336 goto err;
337
338 /* Try decrypting corrupted ciphertexts. */
339 for (n = 0; n < clen; ++n) {
340 ctext[n] ^= 1;
341 num = RSA_private_decrypt(clen, ctext, ptext, key,
342 RSA_PKCS1_OAEP_PADDING);
343 if (!TEST_int_le(num, 0))
344 goto err;
345 ctext[n] ^= 1;
346 }
347
348 /* Test truncated ciphertexts, as well as negative length. */
349 for (n = -1; n < clen; ++n) {
350 num = RSA_private_decrypt(n, ctext, ptext, key,
351 RSA_PKCS1_OAEP_PADDING);
352 if (!TEST_int_le(num, 0))
353 goto err;
354 }
355
356 ret = 1;
357err:
358 RSA_free(key);
359 return ret;
360}
361
362int setup_tests(void)
363{
364 ADD_ALL_TESTS(test_rsa_pkcs1, 3);
365 ADD_ALL_TESTS(test_rsa_sslv23, 3);
366 ADD_ALL_TESTS(test_rsa_oaep, 3);
367 return 1;
368}
